#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African Local Government Association in KwaZulu NatalÂ is working with municipalities, to professionalise the running of local government, and improve service delivery in the province. SALGA is having a Good Governance symposium this week aimed at empowering local government officials. Its KZN Chairperson Thami Ntuli says the gathering will include mayors, speakers and municipal managers. He told eNCA that the aim is to provide clean and good governance. Watch the video above for more details on this story.